**What went well :** 

1.  We were able to pickup Flask fairly soon to be able to develop a microservice

**What could have been better :** 

1.  We had to incur technical debt since the taiga Microservice is not ready, so we will have to come back and refactor when it is ready.
2.  We should build a little more modular code by breaking a single large method/function into smaller methods/functions.
3.  Due to the design of the code, we were not able to unit test, attending to point 2 will help resolve this.

**What we will change for the next sprint :** 

1.  We will build modular code
2.  We will make unit tests
